<br>
People keep saying it's good to use on short fights or low HP mobs or mobs with high resists.  Well what mobs exactly require you to be in melee range exactly or that have such uber high resist rates that nothing with hit them?  Kunark mobs?  Maybe some velious?  If you're a wizard over level 59 and have 23 AAs (minimum) to get Manaburn chances are you're going to be past that stage of the game.  At least some regular nuke will on most mobs in luclin, PoP, LoY, and hell even most of velious.  <br>
<br>
An example of Draught of Ro was given as an example.  Draught of Ro is hardly our best nuke that would be used for DPS.  Ice spear of Destruction w/ Draught of E`ci, Tears of Marr, Strike of Solusek, and some people even use Shock of Magic.  All those Harvest/Mod Rod/Flowing Thought/Bard song/VoQ buffs to help you regen also help you to nuke longer.  Manaburn damage is *capped*, regular damage isn't.  You can only do ~9500ish max.  If a person with 4k mana can do the max, and you have 6k mana, you're essentially wasting 1/3 of your mana pool.  If you have Ancient Greater Concussion or Elemental Leggings managing your aggro should be a lot easier.  On the other hand if you have those you're way beyond most mobs that require you to be in melee range or with uber high resists in everything.<br>
<br>
The fact that it's capped limits how useful it is for mana -&gt; damage.  Verant gimped it so bad so that we couldn't abuse it on higher mobs in PoP.  However we also found a nice use for it...hyper-killing kunark mobs cause they were designed to be weak with low hps by today's standards.  Will manaburn still pack a punch on those mobs?  Yes.  In today's game years and many expansions after should you be wasting AAs on a limited ability?  No.  Get something better. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ravilicuslolf>Ravilicus LoLF</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br>  Posts: 734<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/26/03 12:10 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: heh</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Correct me if I'm wrong, but doesn't Manaburn take aggro now?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Yep, you are wrong.<br>
<br>
Heh, I guess you missed my rather large post just above yours.  Mana Burn generates zip for aggro.  The only time it did was after they &quot;tuned&quot; archery and ranged attacks were generating stupidly high aggro.  They fixed it.<br>
<br>
Level 61+ Draughts are OFTEN used instead of Ice Spear of Solist and Ancient Destruction of Ice (There is no such thing as Spear of Icy Destruction or whatever you called it) because PoP mobs that are remarkablly high level DO have a tendency to resist draughts less frequently.  You land for maximum damage more often with draughts because they have a -50 resist modifier.<br>
<br>
However, the choice or whether or not to use Mana Burn isn't about resists.  The fact that Mana Burn is unresistable is just a side benefit.  I makes the damage reliable.<br>
<br>
The choice or whether or not to use Mana Burn isn't about delivering more or less damage, either.  You aren't going to Mana Burn and then do nothing afterwards.  You will harvest and mod rod and keep nuking like normal.  If you have the proper buffs, gear, AA abilities, and group arrangement you can amp your mana regen considerablly.  This will allow you to nuke after the burn.<br>
<br>
The nuke(s) you choose to use afterwards is irrelevant.  The only question really is &quot;How much damage do I personally need to deliver in this fight&quot;.  If you can deliver this damage FASTER by using Mana Burn, use it.  If you cannot, then don't.  It isn't rocket science.<br>
<br>
It is all about DPS and aggro control.  In fights that last less than 5 minutes, the DPS increase that using Mana Burn gives you is substantial enough to justify it's use IF you are properly prepared.  If you need to have mana after the target is killed, don't use Mana Burn!  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I know this from log parses and having the ability.  I have done it.  I am not speculating. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showMessageRange?topicID=27065.topic&start=1&stop=20>1</a> <b>2</b>  </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showPrevMessage?topicID=27065.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showNextMessage?topicID=27065.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.emailToFriend?topicID=27065.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.threadControl?topicID=27065.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=27065.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/subscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to receive email notification of replies"> Click to receive email notification of replies</a> <br>  <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=27065.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/unsubscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to stop receiving email notification of replies"> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies</a> <br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub140.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" ce